# Data layer (EF Core + PostgreSQL)

## Repositories & Unit of Work
- Generic base `Repository<T>` (primary ctor takes `TacdentDbContext`) exposes
  `GetByIdAsync`/`GetAllAsync`/`AddAsync`/`Update`/`Remove`. Entity-specific repos derive from it
  and add tailored queries via an `IXxxRepository` interface.
- **Repositories never call `SaveChanges`.** Committing is the Unit of Work's job:
  `unitOfWork.SaveChangesAsync(ct)`. One commit per use case.
- Read-only queries use `.AsNoTracking()`. Lookups whose result will be updated/removed are
  **tracked** (no `AsNoTracking`) — keep that distinction.
- New aggregate -> add `IXxxRepository` + `XxxRepository`, expose it on `IUnitOfWork`/`UnitOfWork`,
  and register both in `DependencyInjection.AddDataLayer` as `Scoped`.

## DbContext & configurations
- `TacdentDbContext` exposes `DbSet`s and calls `ApplyConfigurationsFromAssembly`. Put mapping
  in an `IEntityTypeConfiguration<T>` under `Configurations/` — one per entity. Set `HasMaxLength`,
  `IsRequired`, indexes, and store enums as strings via `.HasConversion<string>()`.
- Audit fields are handled centrally by `AuditableEntityInterceptor` (registered in DI and added
  to the context). Don't replicate that logic elsewhere.

## Migrations
- After changing an entity or config: `dotnet ef migrations add <Name>` (the app applies
  migrations automatically on startup via `Database.MigrateAsync()`). Don't hand-edit the model
  snapshot.
